<sect1 id="dir_d622a35e7403102787f31ec94282d34f_1autotoc_md149">
<title>helios::engine::common::types</title><para>Shared context structs for entity-to-entity interactions.</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_d622a35e7403102787f31ec94282d34f_1autotoc_md150">
<title>Types</title><para><table rows="3" cols="2"><row>
<entry thead="yes"><para>Type  </para>
</entry><entry thead="yes"><para>Description  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>InteractionContext</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Base context carrying target, instigator, causer, and contact point  </para>
</entry></row>
<row>
<entry thead="no"><para><computeroutput>DamageContext</computeroutput>  </para>
</entry><entry thead="no"><para>Extends InteractionContext with a damage amount  </para>
</entry></row>
</table>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_d622a35e7403102787f31ec94282d34f_1autotoc_md151">
<title>InteractionContext</title><para>Generic interaction between two entities:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>target</computeroutput> – Entity affected by the interaction</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>instigator</computeroutput> – Entity that initiated the interaction</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>causer</computeroutput> – Entity that directly caused the interaction (e.g. projectile)</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>contact</computeroutput> – World-space contact point</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
</sect1>
<sect1 id="dir_d622a35e7403102787f31ec94282d34f_1autotoc_md152">
<title>DamageContext</title><para>Builds on InteractionContext by adding:<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para><computeroutput>interactionContext</computeroutput> – The underlying interaction</para>
</listitem><listitem><para><computeroutput>damage</computeroutput> – Amount of damage to apply</para>
</listitem></itemizedlist>
</para>
<para>Used by <computeroutput>HealthManager</computeroutput> and <computeroutput>ApplyDamageCommand</computeroutput> to transport damage information from the collision/combat layer to the health system.</para>
<para><hruler/>
</para>
